&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Advanced Clinical Practitioner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for two Advanced Clinical Practitioners to join our Community Services Divisional Team. These post holders will be line managed, and work closely with our Assistant Director of Therapy in Community Services and will work as a key clinician in the integrated clinical vision for the wider Trust and Partner organisations. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have 2 WTE roles available, one ACP will provide clinical therapy leadership for the Intermediate Care and the Urgent Care Pathways and one ACP will focus on our therapeutic Rehabilitation Pathways. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note, this is the advert for the Intermediate Care and Urgent Care ACP role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holders will have a strong therapy background and will be confident clinicians with experience of holistic management of patients with complex conditions and presentations in a variety of settings. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This opportunity is also open for Trainee Advanced Clinical Practitioners (as a Band 7 development role) who will be supported to complete the necessary ACP qualifications.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;em&gt;For a confidential conversation about this role please contact Sophie Markevics, Assistant Director of Therapy – Community Services (07790924395)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: Thursday 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: Thursday 26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are:&lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
